The paper discusses a new hybrid approach for clustering using meta-heuristic optimization techniques and Kalman filtering. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The paper specifically focuses on improving partitional data clustering, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm on several datasets, which suggests that it may fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
